cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with visual recognition tasks and proposes a deep learning framework that incorporates an attention mechanism to improve the performance of structured representation learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves end-to-end learning and optimization, which suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves prediction and classification, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves experiments on standard scene recognition and fine-grained categorization benchmarks, which suggests the involvement of multimedia and information retrieval, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) other likely categories.
